, depending on the\ngroup-velocity dispersion of the host medium. Numerical simulations of the\nmodel equations in the full nonlinear regime, reveal the eixstence of pulse\ntrains the amplitudes of which are enhanced by the radiative recombination\nprocesses. Numerical results for the density of the induced electron plasma\nfeature two distinct regimes of time evolution, depending on the strength of\nthe electron-hole radiative recombination processes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 20 Feb 2021 19:21:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-08"}
